<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/260</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1458</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In connection with my despatch No. 1455
                            of April 14, dealing with the Grand Canal contract, I have the honor to
                            add, in order <pb facs="0382" n="216" xml:id="pg_216"/> to avoid
                            misunderstanding, that when my opinion was asked by Chinese officials
                            concerning the advisability of accepting the suggestion of the American
                            International Corporation with respect to giving to Japanese capitalists
                            a share in the financing of the canal enterprise, I have replied in a
                            sense favorable to the suggestion. * * * Unfortunately the further
                            proposal now revealed that there is to be participation not only in the
                            financing, but also in construction and management, will make our
                            position far more difficult.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Paul S. Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>